post_text:
Update from Pawnee Heights:
The Re-Opening team continues to work hard to develop a safe plan for the reopening of the Pawnee Heights school this fall. The decision has been made to delay the start of school one week to ensure staff has adequate time to prepare for students and proper safety procedures are in place. Enrollment is still scheduled for Tuesday, Wednesday, and Thursday of this week as originally planned. School will officially start on August 27th not August 20th as planned. We will keep you posted with additional information as it becomes available. Please give us a call if you have any questions or concerns.

post_text: Student homework packets will be available tomorrow (April 9th) between 10:30-12:00 at the school in Rozel. The district will continue to use the west door of the building to distribute packets and eventually school lunches. District staff will deliver packets to your car so you will not need to get out. Your students teacher will email you and your student today to notify you if you will have an educational packet that needs to be picked up. Please stay safe and stay home.

post_text: Pawnee Heights will begin a district wide food program beginning on Tuesday, April 14th. We will have lunches and the next days breakfast available in a "grab and go" format on all days that school is scheduled to be in session. Pickup times will be as follows: Rozel at the schools west door from 11:30-12:15, Burdett school from 11:30-12:15 and in Hanston at the Elk Plaza from 11:45-12:30. You will need to pre-order meals for the week by noon the Friday prior to the week you are requesting food service. Please email Tricia Colglazier at triciacolglazier@phtigers.net to request your school meals. As always please stay home and stay safe. For clarification lunches provided by the district will be free of charge for children birth through 18. Also please include in your email to Mrs. Colglazier where you would like you lunches delivered. Thank you!!

post_text: Staff from Pawnee Heights schools worked last week to develop plans to continue providing in educational opportunities to all of our students. The district is also providing devises for students that don‚Äôt have ones at home. We are also working with GBT to provide internet services to families that don‚Äôt have access. Over the past few days everybody should have been contacted by school staff on specific details on how each grades continuous learning plan will look. If you have not been in contact with your students teacher please contact them by email via the school website. The current plan will have homework packet pickup on Thursdays in Rozel, Burdett, and Hanson, this is subject to change but is currently the plan. As more information becomes available we will update everyone. Also, frequently check your email along with the districts Facebook page and website. Stay safe!!

post_text: Tomorrow April 2nd students personal items, music instruments, chrome books, and supplies will be available for pickup. Please enter the parking lot through the West entrance and a school staff member will meet you at the west door. Please do not get out of your vehicle. K through 5th grade students please return your Hoops for Heart money packet. Track athletes are also asked to return your track uniform in a sealed bag. Pickup times for families with last name beginning A through H can begin pickup at 8:30, last names beginning with H through N will start at 9:00, last names beginning O through Z may begin the process at 9:30. Please be patient as we are trying to serve all our students and families. Pick up will be available until 1:30. We will schedule one more pickup time at a later date to accommodate all family schedules. We will provide more information about the upcoming weeks as they become available. Please be safe and stay home if possible.

post_text: Governor Kelly and KSDE Commissioner Dr. Watson has just released a statement that all Kansas schools will be closed through the end of the school year. We are not exactly sure how that format will look moving forward to provide educational services to the students of USD 496. KSDE plans to release additional information tomorrow evening to clarify what those requirements may look like. In the meantime USD 496 will be closed the remainder of this week for deep cleaning of the schools and only essential administrative duties. Spring break scheduled for next week will continue as scheduled. We will update you as soon as more information becomes available. Please be safe.

post_text: Based on KSDE and CDC recommendations, Pawnee Heights USD 496 will be closed March 16 through March 20th. All certified and classified staff will report to work on March 17th. All high school students enrolled in Barton County Community College classes are advised to consult with their professors to make sure all requirements are being meet. All extracurricular activities, in clouding practices and events, are canceled until further notice. We will update you as soon as more information becomes available. Please stay safe. Thank You.

In case you didn't know, regardless if you shop at Caseys or not, you can help any of the schools in our district to win $5,000 just by creating a login at caseys.com/schools by February 14, 2020. Once you have created a login follow these easy steps:
Click on the Rewards tab
School Donations
Enter 67574 as your zip code
Select Pawnee Heights School

Winners are not selected based on purchases, but by the number of entries. In addition, just by creating a login, Casey's will reward you with a FREE single slice of pizza, which you can redeem by clicking on Available Offers under the Rewards tab.

Thank you for taking the time to make a few simple clicks to show your support for our schools!

Scott Goodheart‚ÄéHallowed Hardwood
July 12, 2019 at 10:49 PM ¬∑

On the west side of Pawnee County on Highway 156 sits the community of Rozel. This area has a rich farming tradition, has put together some
successful teams and also produced some famous natives on national level. Pawnee Heights has been one of the communities to bounce back with having to do away with some varsity sports for several years but have had dedication from young people moving back or into the community investing in it and rebuilding the Pawnee Heights name. A famous Rozelian & Pawnee Heights graduate that comes to mind, TCU football coach, Gary Patterson. Another famous PHHS alumni but actually was from Garfield is former K-State distance trackster and Olympian, Christian Smith.

post_text:
School will be dismissed at 12:00 pm this Friday, May 10th, so the faculty, staff, students, and their families will have the opportunity to attend the funeral of Carol Ludlum. Busses will run at that time.

Because of the forecasted possibility of severe weather events moving through Pawnee County, this evening's concert has been postponed to coincide with the Little Rascals track meet scheduled for Wednesday, May 15th. The track meet will begin at 8:45 am and be completed by approximately 10:45 am with the music program to follow at 11:00 am. The music performance will conclude by 11:45 am, students will eat their lunches and finish the day in their classrooms. Regular transportation routes will run at 3:30 pm.

post_text: What better way to travel the world than through music! On Tuesday, March 5th, Pawnee Heights will present a Spring Concert entitled "A World of Music," featuring the fifth through eighth grade musicians. The concert will begin with international folk songs from the fifth and sixth grade bands, followed by the combined seventh and eighth grade band. The program will conclude with the choirs performing works from all over the world. Get ready to go jet-setting from Australia, to Russia, Africa, Europe, and more in this multi-lingual, upbeat concert starting at 7pm in the Rozel gym on March 5th.

IMPORTANT

The Kansas Association of School Boards is assisting our school district in the process of a superintendent search. Their representative, Mr. Gary Sechrist, will host a community forum to gain perspective and insight for the qualities that you will value in the lead administrator of our school district. Please plan to attend the meeting on December 12th at 5:30 p.m. in the Burdett United Methodist Education Center, 502 Elm Street.
